This explains how to setup Jenkins trigger from email.

Following is a good blog that explains it!

https://thesaitech.wordpress.com/2017/10/20/triggering-jenkins-jobs-via-email/
https://github.com/jenkinsci/poll-mailbox-trigger-plugin

Couple of things need to be taken care

1. Install poll mailbox trigger plugin
2. Make following gmail settings 
   - Enable two step verification
   - Create app password and use that instead of gmail password
3. We can send parameter to the Jenkins by mentioning "key=value" in the gmail body
